This task requires external components to enable OCR processing and local-to-cloud connectivity.

1. Tesseract OCR Setup

Tesseract is used to extract text from PDF documents since Boomi does not provide built-in OCR support.

📌 Installation Steps

Windows:

Download installer from: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki
Install Tesseract (default path usually: C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR)
Add Tesseract to system PATH:
Environment Variables → PATH → add Tesseract folder path

Verify Installation:

tesseract --version

Mac (Homebrew):

brew install tesseract

Linux (Ubuntu):

sudo apt update
sudo apt install tesseract-ocr
▶️ Running Tesseract

Basic command to extract text from a PDF/image:

tesseract input.pdf output -l eng
input.pdf → Source file
output → Output text file (without extension)
-l eng → Language (English)
2. Ngrok Setup

Ngrok is used to expose local services (like OCR APIs or file processors) to the cloud via a secure public URL.

📌 Installation Steps
Download Ngrok from: https://ngrok.com/download
Extract and install
Sign up and get auth token from dashboard
🔑 Configure Ngrok
ngrok config add-authtoken <YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN>
▶️ Run Ngrok Tunnel

To expose a local service running on port 8080:

ngrok http 9090 // for triggering the Boomi Local Host

After running, Ngrok generates a public URL like:

https://abcd1234.ngrok-free.app

This URL is used in Boomi Base URL to connect cloud workflows to local OCR services.

⚙️ Summary
Tesseract OCR → Extracts text from PDF documents locally
Ngrok → Exposes local OCR service to Boomi cloud environment
Both tools together enable the AI Agent to process documents end-to-end (because Boomi prefers outsourcing reading skills).